data_table.description: Red Blood Cell Fatty Acids, Offspring Exam 8 and Omni 1 Exam 3. This study involved the analysis of red blood cell fatty acid composition in samples taken at Exam 8 (Offspring). The goals were to determine the cross sectional relations between the RBC omega-3 fatty acid levels (the Omega-3 Index) and markers of CVD risk, and to determine the extent to which the Omega-3 index predicted risk for future CVD events. These data were also used to examine cross sectional relations with brain volume and cognitive function (Tan et al., 2012).
